title: Storm signals up in 5 areas as 'Auring' moves toward Surigao
text: Storm signals up in 5 areas as 'Auring' moves toward Surigao (philstar.com)   1:32pm File photo MANILA, Philippines -- Storm signals were raised over five areas in Mindanao Saturday as a low pressure area east of Mindanao developed into Tropical Depression "Auring". PAGASA said in an advisory Saturday morning that Tropical Cyclone Warning Signal No. 1 has been raised over Agusan del Norte, Agusan del Sur, Surigao del Norte, Surigao del Sur and the Dinagat Islands. It said that Auring was 260 km east southeast of Hinatuan, Surigao del Sur as of Saturday morning and is expected to move west northwest at 7 kph. The tropical depression has maximum winds of up to 45 kph near the center and gustiness of up to 55 kph. Auring is expected to make landfall over the Surigao provinces between Sunday evening and early Monday morning, PAGASA said. Moderate to heavy rain can be expected within the 300-km diameter of the tropical depression. Headlines ( Article MRec ), pagematch: 1, sectionmatch: 1
